1️⃣ LOGICAL REASONING – DIRECTION SENSE

This topic tests:

Spatial thinking
Attention to direction
Logical movement tracking
🔹 A. BASIC DIRECTIONS (VERY IMPORTANT)
        North (↑)
West (←)     East (→)
        South (↓)
🔹 B. TURN RULES
Facing North:
Right → East
Left → West
Facing South:
Right → West
Left → East
Facing East:
Right → South
Left → North
Facing West:
Right → North
Left → South
🔹 Example 1

A person walks 10m North, then turns right and walks 5m.

👉 Final direction?

Facing North → right = East

Answer: East

🔹 Example 2

Walk 5m East → turn left → walk 3m

Facing East → left = North

Answer: North

